      src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/DI/EndpointMappingExtensions.cs (+MapAdminJobsEndpoints call at end of MapDomainEndpoints)
    </files-modified>
    <design-decisions>
      <decision>IBackgroundJobStore extended with GetRecentRunsAsync(jobId, limit, ct) returning a NEW public record BackgroundJobRunRecord. Public projection of internal InMemoryBackgroundJobStore.RunRecord; surfaces canonical Status string (Succeeded/Failed/InProgress) so the Dataverse-backed store in task 023+ doesn't need to re-canonicalize from sprk_backgroundjobrun option-set values.</decision>
      <decision>SchedulingModule.cs registers ScheduledJobRegistry + InMemoryBackgroundJobStore (as IBackgroundJobStore + concrete) UNCONDITIONALLY per bff-extensions.md §F.1 — endpoints map unconditionally so dependencies must too. ADR-032 N/A (real services, not kill-switches). When task 023+ swaps in the Dataverse-backed store, the registration site is this single module.</decision>
      <decision>JobsEndpoints.cs uses Cronos directly for NextScheduledOn via a local ParseCron helper that mirrors ScheduledJobHost.ParseCron (5-field minute-precision OR 6-field seconds). Cron-format failures log Warning + omit NextScheduledOn rather than 500 the whole admin list.</decision>
      <decision>Orphan-handler tolerance: jobs registered with ScheduledJobRegistry but missing a definition in IBackgroundJobStore surface with Enabled=false + empty cron + NextScheduledOn=null. Mirrors ScheduledJobHost's same tolerance and lets operators spot "handler registered but no definition" misconfigs via the admin UI.</decision>
      <decision>Authorization model: existing SystemAdmin policy at AuthorizationModule.cs:241 per Q6 owner clarification — NOT a new PlatformAdmin policy. Precedent: RagEndpoints admin group uses the same policy.</decision>
      <decision>Test fixture (AdminJobsTestFixture) separate from CustomWebAppFactory/WorkspaceTestFixture: needs per-test admin/non-admin/none auth selection via X-Test-Role header (X-Test-Role:admin → roles=SystemAdmin claim; user → roles=User; missing → 401). The custom FakeAuthHandler that hardcodes SystemAdmin roles wouldn't work because we explicitly need a 403 path.</decision>
      <decision>Reserved comment blocks in JobsEndpoints.cs explicitly delimit task-021 and task-022 sections to minimize merge conflict surface — those tasks append handlers without touching task-020 code.</decision>
      <decision>Test reset between tests via reflection on InMemoryBackgroundJobStore._runs/_jobs + ScheduledJobRegistry._jobs ConcurrentDictionaries. Production code intentionally has no Clear() (single-host invariant); tests need symmetric teardown to avoid inter-test pollution given the shared fixture.</decision>
    </design-decisions>
    <coordination-with-021-022>
      Tasks 021 + 022 will ALSO touch JobsEndpoints.cs. To minimize merge friction:
      - This task owns the GET /api/admin/jobs handler + the GET /{jobId}/status handler + shared helpers (BuildSummaryFromRuns, ToJobRunDetail, ParseCron).
      - The MapGroup + reserved // ===== Task 021 / Task 022 ===== // comment blocks are at clearly-delimited lines in MapAdminJobsEndpoints — those tasks append after the GET /{jobId}/status block.
      - All three tasks share the helper methods; tasks 021/022 should NOT modify them without coordinating back to this PR.
    </coordination-with-021-022>
    <verification>
      adr-check (self): PASS — ADR-001 (in-process), ADR-008 (RequireAuthorization at MapGroup level, no global middleware), ADR-010 (concretes + interface justified ≥2 impls), ADR-029 (publish-size measured +0.02 MB), ADR-032 N/A. TreatWarningsAsErrors honored on Spaarke.Scheduling; BFF has 0 new warnings from task code.
      bff-extensions §A/§F: PASS — Placement Justification ✅, ADRs cited ✅, publish-size ✅, no new CRUD→AI dep ✅, feature-module DI ✅. §F.1 asymmetric-registration PASS — endpoints map unconditionally + services register unconditionally.
      AC verification: AC-2.5 ✅ (403 non-admin test passes), GET /api/admin/jobs returns list ✅, GET /{jobId}/status returns detail with 10 runs ✅, 404 unknown ✅, AC-2.7 failed-run ErrorMessage surfaces ✅.
    </verification>
